Run topological sort on the dependency graph (modules as nodes, imports as edges) to produce waves: wave 0 = leaf modules with no internal deps, wave N = modules whose deps are all in waves < N. Audit each wave in parallel (one reviewer/agent per module), gating wave N+1 on wave N completion so findings propagate upward. For each module capture: public API surface, invariants, untrusted inputs, side effects, and known CVEs in transitive deps. Break cycles by collapsing SCCs (via Tarjan) into single audit units. Persist results in a per-module report keyed by commit SHA so re-audits diff cleanly. Prioritize within a wave by blast radius (reverse-dependency count × sensitivity score). Track coverage in a matrix: rows = modules, columns = audit dimensions (security, perf, correctness, licensing). Stop criterion: every module has a green report at HEAD or an explicit waiver.